article.description: Ehab Amin scored a career-high 26 points and tied a career best with nine rebounds to help Texas A&M-Corpus Christi beat Northwestern State 89-79 Tuesday night.
article.headline: Amin's career day leads TAMU-CC past Northwestern St. 89-79
article.linkText: Amin's career day leads TAMU-CC past Northwestern St. 89-79
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. -- Ehab Amin scored a career-high 26 points and tied a career best with nine rebounds to help Texas A&M-Corpus Christi beat Northwestern State 89-79 Tuesday night. Amin made 8 of 11 field goals, including 2 of 4 from 3-point range, and had three steals. Hameed Ali had 13 points, a career-high 12 rebounds and five steals for the Islanders (14-3, 5-0 Southland Conference), who have won seven games in a row and 14 of their last 15. Brandon Pye scored 17, including three 3s, and Joe Kilgore added 12 points, seven rebounds and four blocked shots. A 3-pointer by Sabri Thompson pulled Northwestern State (3-13, 0-6) within 33-31 with 3:53 left in the first half, but the Islanders scored eight of the next 10 points and took a 44-35 lead into the break. Amin's layup with 15:31 to play capped a 9-0 run and made it 53-38 and Northwestern State trailed by at least seven from there. Ishmael Lane led the Demons with 18 points and 11 rebounds.
